text: Otakar Kouba (born October 24, 1906, date of death unknown) was a Czechoslovak canoeist who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics. He was born in Prague. In 1936 he and his partner Ludvík Klíma finished fifth in the folding K-2 10000 m event. ==References== *Otakar Kouba's profile at Sports Reference.com Category:1906 births Category:Canoeists at the 1936 Summer Olympics Category:Czechoslovak male canoeists Category:Olympic canoeists of Czechoslovakia Category:Year of death missing
